casebody.data:
Oliver AGUERO, VI, Appellant,
v.
DEPARTMENT OF FINANCIAL SERVICES, Appellee. No. 3D17-0171 District Court of Appeal of Florida, Third District. Opinion filed November 29, 2017
Rehearing Denied January 4, 2018 Oliver Aguero, VI, in proper person. Matthew R. Daley, Assistant General Counsel (Tallahassee), for appellee. Before SUAREZ, LAGOA and SCALES, JJ. PER CURIAM.

Upon review of Appellant's initial brief, we find no preliminary basis for reversal has been demonstrated. We, therefore, summarily affirm the order on appeal. See Fla. R. App. 9.315(a).
